This device has no model information / FCC ID on the label. :The tagline on the label is, however, '''High Power AP/Router'''. :It has two checkboxes - one for 400mW and one for 1W. ::The 1W checkbox is marked.
"AWR1114gA" is silkscreened on the board of the unit (hence the name of this entry). :The board is using all '''JACKCON''' capacitors.
The device looks to be the [http://www.wireless-lan-manufacturer.com/indoor-ap-router/01.htm '''ARGtek''' (''Power King'') ARG-1206] ('''Afoundry''' is ''or is associated with'' '''ARGtek'''). :'''Afoundry''' is ''presumed'' to be the manufacturer.. but this may be incorrect.
The power adapter included with the device may be a '''DVE''' DSA-15P-12 US 120150 (100-240VAC ~ 50/60Hz, 0.5A -> 12VDC, 1.25A).
